Introduction

Lee Jun Young, also known as Jun, is a South Korean singer, rapper, and actor under JFlex Entertainment. He was first known for joining the boy group U-KISS in 2014.

In 2017, he participated in competition show "The Unit." He ended up as the male contestant with the most votes, and was able to debut as a member of project group UNB from 2018 until their disbandment in 2019. He then made his solo debut on December 5, 2019 with the single album "Gallery" under his full name, Lee Jun Young.

Besides performing, Jun Young is also known for starring in dramas such as "Class of Lies", "Please Don't Date Him", "D.P", "Imitation", and "Let Me Be Your Knight".
